name: Beheaded Medal
description: This medal features a reproduction of my "Beheaded" print. It comes set in a .75"x.50" brass pendant with an antique/aged look. Following France's "Reign of Terror", those who narrowly escaped the guillotine as well as the relatives of those who weren't so lucky wore red ribbons around their neck at what would have been the point of impact with the blade. This image of a beheaded woman hangs from a red velvet ribbon that recalls this tradition. The image inside has been treated to give it an antique/aged to match. A layer of resin is set on top to protect and seal the image within the pendant. These medals are a unique and fun accessory to add to any outfit – shirts, vests, jackets, everything! The pin clasp on the back makes it easy to wear securely anywhere. The medal measures approximately 4 inches from top to bottom. Please note that your medal may look slightly different than the one pictured. Some small bubbles may be present in the clear coating as the resin process can cause variability in the finished product. Visit our Etsy or Shop for more unique prints, tees, and more!

This cute little man is stuffed with 100% polyester stuffing. He is sewn with super strong quilting thread for extra durability. All materials used are machine washable. Whether you want to set him on a table as a conversation piece or give him as a gift to someone to love, this anatomical man is sure to get a lot of attention!
